notes: an-and, ghao-wheat, thi-with, puri-puri(dish/indian bread), banayo-prepared

english: And offered them to the goddess.
notes: banatanin-after preparing/after making, deevini-to goddess, chadayo-offered

english: Then, by divine grace, the mud transformed into real sheera.
banjara: janna, deevire anugrah eethi, dhud asli sheera re nai badalgo
notes: janna-the, deevire-of goddess, anugrah-grace, eethi-with, dhud-mud, asli-real, sheera re-of sheera(sweet), nai-like, badalgo-transformed/changed

banjara: ghao jakon asli puri re nai badalgo
notes: ghao-wheat, jakon-that is/ therefore, asli-real, puri re-of puri(indian bread), nai-like, badalgo-changed/transformed.

english: This miracle established his divine nature.
banjara: ee chamatkar eethi vor mai deever nai che jako svabhaav baar padi
notes: ee-this, chamatkar-miracle, eethi-with, vor-hi,s mai-inside, deever nai-godly/ like god/divine, che jako-being/is there, svabhaav-nature, baar-out, padi-fell

english: Those who witnessed this miracle understood immediately.
banjara: hannu veejanna kun kun dite ko vondun jannaz samaj aavgi
notes: hannu-like that, veejanna-happened, kun kun-who all, dite ko-saw, vondun-they, jannaz-than only, samaj-understood, aavgi-came

english: This was not an ordinary child.
notes: ee-his/this, saadharan-simple/odinary, chora-boy, koni ken - not so.
Vu-he/that, bhagvaneero-of god, amsh-part, che keen-exist/is there

banjara: Jagadamba deevi reej aashirvaad che keen
notes: Jagadamba deevi-Jagadamba deevi, reej-only of, aashirvaad-blessing, che keen- is there

english: From that day forward, he was recognized as spiritually awakened.
banjara: undaadeethi,  vo se deeveer nai dheken lagpade.
notes: undaadeethi-from that day,  vo se-all of them, deeveer-of god/divine, nai-like, dheken-seen/saw/seeing, lagpade-happened,happening
